Class DTCMetaParam

java.lang.Object
  java.util.Observable
      net.sourceforge.JDash.ecu.param.Parameter
          net.sourceforge.JDash.ecu.param.MetaParameter
              net.sourceforge.JDash.ecu.param.DTCMetaParam
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.util.Observer, DoubleParameter, StringParameter
public class DTCMetaParam
extends MetaParameter
implements StringParameter

DTCs are a different thing all together. JDash was created to be a real-time display of sensor values, and DTCs don't exactly fit into this definition. Well.. mostly. So.. A special type of Meta parameter was created for DTCs. It's up to each implementation of a monitor to detect any and all configured DTCMetaParam objects within the parameter registry and deal with them accordingly.

public java.lang.String toString()
